# ─────────────  _headers  (place this in the *publish* folder you deploy)  ─────────────
# All comments start with #.  Every non‑comment line is interpreted by Netlify!

# One catch‑all rule applies to every request (HTML, JS, CSS, and even redirects)
# Indent header lines by exactly two spaces.
#
# Adjust the Access‑Control‑Allow‑Origin line if you need to lock it down to a
# specific site or open it up to everyone.

 /*
   # --- Caching: force browsers to fetch a fresh copy every time -------------
   Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate
   Pragma: no-cache
   Expires: 0

   # --- CORS: allow fetch() from your main site ------------------------------
   Access-Control-Allow-Origin: https://member.archmarketing.org
   Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, OPTIONS
   Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type

   # If your fetch() includes cookies or an Authorization header, uncomment:
   # Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true
